not getting schoolarships after receiving education for free all my life
I have been wanting to further my studies in an European country but since i live in a small economically challenged country, it is a bit impossible to apply for schools as a foreigner
Before i was born, my parents came to South Africa for construction jobs. So my parents dont have any papers or money to emigrate, it will be much cheaper trying to study here but atleast in my country
What can i do so that i can get accepted by a school in Europe or the US without paying a big amount or physical exams

Hi Shana

If you are under 18 you can apply to your National European Agency which helps young people under 18 study in other EU countries.
